Disk notes: The SPEC CPU tests use a 400 GB partition
created from 3x Sun StorageTek 6140 stripe sets.  The
partition was created in 3 steps: 1. Each 6140 stripe
set (RAID 0) is based on 8x 146 GB 15,000 RPM Seagate
ST3146954FC FC-AL disks.  2. Solaris views these as 3
logical units (LUNs) which are striped together (RAID
0) to make a 3 TB volume using Solaris Volume Manager
(SVM).  3. Lastly, SVM is then used to create one 400
GB soft partition for use by the CPU2006 output_root.
